                "institute": "1USATNL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using TUNL's",
                "atomic beam polarized ion source and FN-tandem",
                "accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Deuterated liquid scintillator, equivalent to NE232",
                "was used as an active target. Scintillator was in a",
                "glass cylinder of 4.2 cm in diameter and 6.4 cm high."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Six pairs of NE213 liquid scintillation",
                "detectors surrounded the central deuterated active",
                "target detector. Side detectors scintillator diameter",
                "was 12.7cm and thickness of either 5.1 or 6.1 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For each elastic scattering event a",
                "coincidence between central detector and side",
                "detector was required. Analysing power was determined",
                "from the asymmetry between the left and right",
                "detectors. In order to cancel instrumental asymmetries,",
                "the ion source flipped the deuteron spin orientation",
                "between up and down at a rate of 10 Hz."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLNS",
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Polarized neutrons were produced via the",
                "D(d,n)3He source reaction at 0deg. The deuteron beam",
                "current reaching the gas cell was typically 1.1 mu-A",
                "and the energy spread was +-0.28 MeV.",
                "The beam polarization, was monitored with a",
                "polarimeter constructed of an active gas cell filled",
                "to 100 atm with a mixture of 95% 4He gas and 5% xenon",
                "gas, and two neutron side detectors placed at theta",
                "lab 112 deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
